Medical education in [[Thailand]] was pioneered by [[King Chulalongkorn]], who founded the country's first [[Medical school]] called the "School of Medical Practitioners" at [[Siriraj Hospital]] in 1889, now became the [[Faculty of Medicine Siriraj Hospital, Mahidol University]]. There are now 20 Institutions that offers medical programs nationwide, most of them public. Graduates will receive a [[Doctor of Medicine|MD]] degree (Doctor of Medicine), equivalent to [[Bachelor of Medicine]]. Most of these schools also provide postgraduate and specialist programs. The Medical Council of Thailand is responsible for verifying all curricula. 

